        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I am trying to implement a solution that ensures that any given request never takes longer than a certain number of seconds. In the current implementation however it is only possible to set a timeout for the initial connect, but not for the time it takes for the server to actually return the entire request.\n\nIn PEAR::HTTP_Request they provide a listener solution for this (which also enables download progress bars):\nhttp:\/\/cvs.php.net\/viewvc.cgi\/pear\/HTTP_Request\/Request\/Listener.php?view=markup\n"
        },
